caption: Hidden gem in Chinatown. The tacos were Asian fusion and really good. The owner was also really friendly.

Charming stall at the inner courtyard entrance to the food hall. The chef himself or an assistant will take your order and prepare the food then and there. We got the excellent Szechuan 🍆 and 🐖 belly 🌮 with annato-hued rice and black beans. Soft 🌮 shells were perfectly warmed with slightly crisp edges. We had haupia topped with persimmon and lilikoi for dessert. I'll have to come back to try the peppered beef and chicken 🌮 options, as well as the tomatillo stew!
Food is fresh! Very tasty... best of all the Dude remembers their customers! Awesome!

My wife and I came here for lunch today for the first time.  We ordered the pork belly and braised beef tacos.  The pork belly tacos were the stars but the braised beef was delicious as well.  The rice and beans were a little under seasoned but good overall.  Definitely an interesting take on tacos and and surprisingly good!
